Atop a hill, high above where the trees no longer touch the sky, a lonely keeper stood over a box. 

"It's time Martin".

Martin didn't bother to spin around. Although he hadn't heard the intruder enter the mountain top home, he had been expecting him for years. He took one last look at the box and sighed.

"Don't..." the figure whispered, but it was too late. As Martin pulled the Emperor's heart out of the box, the shadowed figured lunged. 

